    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "Made of materials scavenged from wild places, a *druid's crown* can be rebuilt for a variety of benefits. The crown grants you a +1 item bonus to a skill, and can be activated to cast a spell, both depending on the material used to build the crown, as listed on the table below. If you invest and wear *living mantle* along with the crown, the crown's item bonus increases by 1 and its spell's DC rises to 27.  \n   \n You can invest this item only if you're a druid. When you do, as a 10-minute activity that has the manipulate trait, you can disassemble and rebuild the crown with different materials, changing its item bonus and spell accordingly.",
        "sections": [
            {
                "name": "",
                "type": "section",
                "text": "|  |  |  |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **Material** | **Item Bonus** | **Spell** |\n| Antlers | Intimidation | *Enlarge* |\n| Flowers | Diplomacy | *Animal allies* |\n| Leaves | Stealth | *One with Plants* |",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Intimidation",
                        "alt": "Intimidation",
                        "game-obj": "Skills",
                        "aonid": 7
